<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-660-407  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 660 407.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  Nov 26 1990 n618 p81(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>EDAC influences changes in DAC. (Electronic Design AutomationCompanies; Design Automation Conference)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Goering, Richard.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The recently formed Electronic Design Automation Companies (EDAC)trade association has already achieved a notable success,persuading the Design Automation Conference to better serve theinterests of participating vendors by providing better support forexhibitors.andP;  Changes to be implemented include the addition of an'industrial' track to feature sessions on management issues,improvements in exhibition presentation and location, and a day offree access to the exhibits without having to pay for thetechnical program.andP;  EDAC is also taking action in support ofstandards and is seeking out legislative issues to become involvedin.andP;  As an international organization, EDAC will advocate freetrade.andP;  EDAC's membership is comprised of more than 45 membersrepresenting essentially every major EDA firm, with bothworkstation and microcomputer suppliers represented.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Electronic Design AutomationTrade and Professional AssociationsDesign Automation ConferenceElectronic Design Automation Cos..andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>